wikipedia_page.main: Sir Frank William Wills (17 August 1852 – 26 March 1932) of Berkeley Square, Bristol, England, was a member of the Wills tobacco family, who became a noted British architect and went on to serve as Lord Mayor of Bristol.

response: St George's Catholic Church, Boreham Road, was built in 1922 to designs of Bristol architect Sir Frank William Wills. St Giles' Garrison Church, Imber Road, was built in 1968.

Wills was the son of William Day Wills and a cousin of Sir Edward Payson Wills Bt, Sir Frederick Wills Bt, Sir Frank William Wills Kt, and Henry Overton Wills III, first chancellor of the University of Bristol.
* Frank William Wills (1852–1932), British architect and Lord Mayor of Bristol
**Sir Frank William Wills (1852–1932), Knight Bachelor, a noted British architect and Lord Mayor of Bristol.
